Package: ldaOptim
Type: Package
Title: Systematic Parameter Optimization for LDA Topic Modeling
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Ayse D.", "Lokmanoglu", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "alokman@bu.edu"),
    person("Dror", "Walter", role = c("aut")),
    person("Yotam", "Ophir", role = c("aut"))
  )
Description: Provides systematic optimization and fitting workflow for Latent 
    Dirichlet Allocation (LDA) topic modeling. Implements cross-validation for 
    alpha parameter optimization, multiple evaluation metrics (Griffiths2004, 
    CaoJuan2009, Arun2010, Deveaud2014) for finding optimal number of topics (Murzintcev, N., 2020), 
    parallel model fitting, and comprehensive Excel export functionality. Based 
    on methodology from Jacobi et al. (2016) and provides a modern replacement 
    for the deprecated ldatuning package. This package operates on a DocumentTermMatrix input, which users construct from their raw text data using their preferred text preprocessing and tokenization methods.
